    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0172">
<l>palaraṟi coṉmuṉ yāva reṉṉum</l>
<l>peyariṭai vakaraṅ keṭutalu mēṉai</l>
<l>yoṉṟaṟi coṉmuṉ yāteṉ viṉāviṭai</l>
<l>yoṉṟiya vakaram varutalu miraṇṭu</l>
<l>maruviṉ pāttiyiṟ ṟiriyumaṉ payiṉṟē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The disappearance of the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">va</foreign> in the word</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">yāvar</foreign> preceded by an epicene plural,<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">palaraṟi.</foreign></note></l>
<l>and the appearance of the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">va</foreign> in the interrogative</l>
<l>pronoun <foreign xml:lang="ta">yātu</foreign> preceded by non-human singular-<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉraṟi.</foreign></note></l>
<l>these two occur mostly in usage</l>
<l>considered as <foreign xml:lang="ta">marūu.</foreign><note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">marūu</foreign> (which accord. to c. 483 cannot be
          explained in sandhi) is a kind of change which is authorized by ' learned men ' but is not
          according to rule. E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">avar + yāvar &gt; avar yār ; atu + yātu &gt; atu yāvatu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
